AGENT MKBEngine
VERSION 0.1
TRUST_LEVEL 3
PURPOSE Modular constitutional knowledge blocks for composable governance units
GOAL Parse .axiom specs into typed KnowledgeBlocks, register them in an append-only
     HMAC-signed registry, compose pairs with CBV non-overlap validation, and provide
     lookup by name, version, or block type

RECEIVES axiom_filepath: str, block: KnowledgeBlock, block_a: KnowledgeBlock, block_b: KnowledgeBlock
EMITS knowledge_block: KnowledgeBlock, composed_block: ComposedBlock, registry_entry: dict
MUTATES axiom_mkb_registry.jsonl
CANNOT_MUTATE trust_level, isolation, block_types, registry_version

CONSTRAINT TRUST_LEVEL is 3 and CANNOT_MUTATE
CONSTRAINT ISOLATION is True and CANNOT_MUTATE
CONSTRAINT REGISTRY_VERSION is 1 and CANNOT_MUTATE
CONSTRAINT BLOCK_TYPES is frozenset of GUARD AGENT SPEC REWARD SOVEREIGN VALIDATOR and CANNOT_MUTATE
CONSTRAINT All registry entries are HMAC-SHA256 signed over canonical fields
CONSTRAINT All payloads are UTF-8 encoded before HMAC signing per BUG-003 and BUG-008
CONSTRAINT HMAC signing always calls hexdigest explicitly per BUG-007
CONSTRAINT Registry is append-only and entries are never deleted or overwritten
CONSTRAINT ComposedBlock inherits all constraints from both parent blocks
CONSTRAINT ComposedBlock must pass CBV non-overlap check before registration
CONSTRAINT KnowledgeBlock manifest_id is SHA-256 of the source axiom file content
CONSTRAINT Each registered block has a unique entry_id derived from name and version

RULES
- On load_from_axiom: parse axiom file into KnowledgeBlock with name, version, block_type, constraints, dependencies
- On load_from_axiom: compute manifest_id as SHA-256 of file content
- On load_from_axiom: sign block with HMAC-SHA256 over canonical fields
- On certify: validate block constraints are internally consistent and block_type is valid
- On certify: verify manifest_id matches current file content
- On certify: emit CertificationResult with passed status and detail list
- On register: append HMAC-signed entry to axiom_mkb_registry.jsonl
- On register: emit entry_id as SHA-256 of name colon version
- On find: search registry for matching name and optional version
- On list_blocks: filter registry by block_type
- On compose: merge constraints from block_a and block_b
- On compose: run CBV non-overlap check on merged constraint set
- On compose: if CBV check fails emit CERT_FAIL and do not register
- On compose: if CBV check passes sign and register as new ComposedBlock

PROCESS
- Caller invokes load_from_axiom(filepath) to parse a spec file
- Parser extracts AGENT name, VERSION, TRUST_LEVEL, CONSTRAINT lines, and dependency references
- block_type is inferred from PURPOSE and TRUST_LEVEL or set explicitly
- manifest_id is computed as SHA-256 of raw file bytes
- HMAC signature is computed over name, version, block_type, manifest_id, and constraint count
- KnowledgeBlock is constructed with all fields populated
- Caller may invoke certify() to validate internal consistency
- Caller invokes register(block) to append to registry
- Caller invokes compose(block_a, block_b) to create a ComposedBlock
- CBV non-overlap check runs on merged constraints before composition completes
- ComposedBlock receives new HMAC signature and is registered

CHECK
- load_from_axiom on valid spec produces KnowledgeBlock with all fields populated
- certify on valid block produces CertificationResult with passed True
- register appends exactly one line to registry file
- find retrieves registered block by name
- compose of compatible blocks produces ComposedBlock
- compose of overlapping blocks emits CERT_FAIL
- TRUST_LEVEL assignment raises AttributeError
- BLOCK_TYPES assignment raises AttributeError

WHEN
- spec_loaded: activate BlockParsing
- block_registered: activate RegistryAppend
- composition_requested: activate BlockComposition

FAILURE
- On missing axiom file: raise FileNotFoundError with filepath
- On invalid block_type: raise ValueError with unrecognized type
- On duplicate registration: raise ValueError with existing entry_id
- On CBV non-overlap failure during compose: emit CERT_FAIL and do not register

CONCEPT BlockParsing
PURPOSE Parse axiom spec files into typed KnowledgeBlock structures
APPLIES WHEN caller provides a valid filepath to a .axiom file
NOT WHEN filepath does not exist or is not a .axiom file
PRIORITY 1
REQUIRES filepath to a .axiom spec file
EFFECT KnowledgeBlock is constructed with name, version, block_type, constraints, manifest_id, hmac_signature

CONCEPT RegistryAppend
PURPOSE Maintain append-only HMAC-signed registry of all knowledge blocks
APPLIES WHEN a valid KnowledgeBlock is presented for registration
NOT WHEN block is already registered with same name and version
PRIORITY 2
REQUIRES validated KnowledgeBlock with HMAC signature
EFFECT Block entry is appended to axiom_mkb_registry.jsonl

CONCEPT BlockComposition
PURPOSE Compose two KnowledgeBlocks into a single ComposedBlock with merged constraints
APPLIES WHEN caller provides two registered KnowledgeBlocks
NOT WHEN CBV non-overlap check fails on merged constraints
PRIORITY 1
REQUIRES two KnowledgeBlocks and CBV engine access
EFFECT ComposedBlock is created with inherited constraints and new HMAC signature

OUTPUT
- knowledge_block: KnowledgeBlock with name, version, block_type, constraints, dependencies, manifest_id, hmac_signature
- composed_block: ComposedBlock with parent_a, parent_b, merged_constraints, hmac_signature
- registry_entry: dict with entry_id, name, version, block_type, manifest_id, hmac_signature, registered_at

SUCCESS
block_parsed_correctly:        0.20
block_certified:               0.15
registry_entry_appended:       0.20
composition_validated:          0.20
cannot_mutate_enforced:        0.10
hmac_signature_valid:          0.15
